   "source": [
    "# 🧭 Cross-Absolute Selection Principle (CASP)\n",
    "\n",
    "## 📘 Formal Definition\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Definition (CASP):** A mediated interaction between two Absolute Entities is valid if and only if it minimizes the cross-absolute interaction action, maintains entropic compatibility within tolerance δ, and maximizes directional coherence, subject to irreducibility constraints.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 🔬 Theoretical Foundations\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Ontological Context\n",
    "This notebook builds directly on the transfinite mediators from `05_transfinite_interaction_chains.ipynb`, extending our understanding of cross-absolute interactions through rigorous mathematical constraints.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 🔷 Core Postulates\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Postulate I: Minimal Interaction Action\n",
    "**Ontological Derivation:** Mapped from axioms of irreducibility and finite embedding projection.\n",
    "\n",
    "$$ \\mathcal{A}_{\\text{min}} = \\arg \\min_{M \\in \\mathcal{M}} \\| S_1 M S_2^T \\|_F $$\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Postulate II: Entropic Compatibility\n",
    "**Constraint:** Entropy leak must be minimally bounded.\n",
    "\n",
    "$$ \\delta = \\frac{|\\epsilon_1 - \\mathrm{Tr}(I I^T)|}{\\epsilon_1} \\leq 1 \\times 10^{-6} $$\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Postulate III: Directional Coherence Maximization\n",
    "**Normalized Interaction Potential:**\n",
    "\n",
    "$$ \\max \\left( \\cos(\\langle S_1 M, S_2 \\rangle) \\right) $$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Essential Scientific Computing Imports\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import scipy.optimize as optimize\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "# Advanced Visualization Configuration\n",
    "plt.style.use('seaborn')\n",
    "np.set_printoptions(precision=4, suppress=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class CASPViolation(Exception):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Exception raised for CASP interaction constraint violations.\"\"\"\n",
    "    pass\n",
    "\n",
    "class AbsoluteEntity:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Representation of an Absolute Entity with sophisticated constraints.\"\"\"\n",
    "    def __init__(self, signature, state):\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        Initialize an Absolute Entity with rigorous validation.\n",
    "        \n",
    "        Args:\n",
    "            signature (np.ndarray): Symmetric signature matrix\n",
    "            state (np.ndarray): Entity state vector\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        assert signature.shape[0] == signature.shape[1], \"Signature must be square\"\n",
    "        assert np.allclose(signature, signature.T), \"Signature must be symmetric\"\n",
    "        assert state.shape[0] == signature.shape[0], \"State dimension mismatch\"\n",
    "        \n",
    "        self.signature = signature\n",
    "        self.state = state\n",
    "        self.entropy = np.trace(signature @ signature.T)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def cosine_similarity(a, b):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Compute normalized cosine similarity between vectors.\"\"\"\n",
    "    norm_a = np.linalg.norm(a)\n",
    "    norm_b = np.linalg.norm(b)\n",
    "    return np.dot(a, b) / (norm_a * norm_b)\n",
    "\n",
    "def evaluate_casp(entity_a, entity_b, mediator, tolerance=1e-6):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Comprehensive CASP interaction evaluation.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Args:\n",
    "        entity_a (AbsoluteEntity): First absolute entity\n",
    "        entity_b (AbsoluteEntity): Second absolute entity\n",
    "        mediator (np.ndarray): Interaction mediator matrix\n",
    "        tolerance (float): Entropy violation threshold\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "        dict: Comprehensive interaction metrics\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    # Compute Information Tensor\n",
    "    I = entity_a.signature @ mediator @ entity_b.signature.T\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Interaction Action (Frobenius Norm)\n",
    "    action = np.linalg.norm(I, ord='fro')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Entropy Gap Calculation\n",
    "    trace_proj = np.trace(I @ I.T)\n",
    "    entropy_gap = abs(entity_a.entropy - trace_proj)\n",
    "    entropy_leak = entropy_gap / entity_a.entropy\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Directional Coherence\n",
    "    coherence = cosine_similarity(\n",
    "        (entity_a.signature @ mediator).flatten(), \n",
    "        entity_b.signature.flatten()\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Interaction Classification\n",
    "    if entropy_leak > tolerance or coherence < 0:\n",
    "        interaction_type = \"Entropic Conflict\"\n",
    "    elif action < tolerance:\n",
    "        interaction_type = \"Resonant Convergence\"\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        interaction_type = \"Directional Collapse\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return {\n",
    "        'InformationTensor': I,\n",
    "        'InteractionAction': action,\n",
    "        'EntropyLeak': entropy_leak,\n",
    "        'DirectionalCoherence': coherence,\n",
    "        'InteractionType': interaction_type\n",
    "    }"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def optimize_mediator(entity_a, entity_b, initial_guess=None):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Find optimal mediator that minimizes CASP interaction action.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Args:\n",
    "        entity_a (AbsoluteEntity): First absolute entity\n",
    "        entity_b (AbsoluteEntity): Second absolute entity\n",
    "        initial_guess (np.ndarray, optional): Initial mediator guess\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "        np.ndarray: Optimized mediator matrix\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    def objective(M_flat):\n",
    "        M = M_flat.reshape(entity_a.signature.shape[0], entity_b.signature.shape[0])\n",
    "        result = evaluate_casp(entity_a, entity_b, M)\n",
    "        return result['InteractionAction']\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Initial guess if not provided\n",
    "    if initial_guess is None:\n",
    "        initial_guess = np.random.randn(\n",
    "            entity_a.signature.shape[0] * entity_b.signature.shape[0]\n",
    "        )\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Optimization\n",
    "    result = optimize.minimize(\n",
    "        objective, \n",
    "        initial_guess, \n",
    "        method='BFGS'\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return result.x.reshape(\n",
    "        entity_a.signature.shape[0], \n",
    "        entity_b.signature.shape[0]\n",
    "    )"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Comprehensive Simulation Setup\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)  # Reproducible randomness\n",
    "\n",
    "# Generate Absolute Entities\n",
    "A_sig = np.random.rand(4, 4)\n",
    "A_sig = 0.5 * (A_sig + A_sig.T)  # Symmetric\n",
    "B_sig = np.random.rand(4, 4)\n",
    "B_sig = 0.5 * (B_sig + B_sig.T)  # Symmetric\n",
    "\n",
    "A = AbsoluteEntity(A_sig, np.random.rand(4))\n",
    "B = AbsoluteEntity(B_sig, np.random.rand(4))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Optimize Mediator\n",
    "M_optimized = optimize_mediator(A, B)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Evaluate CASP\n",
    "results = evaluate_casp(A, B, M_optimized)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Detailed Metrics Reporting\n",
    "print(\"🔬 CASP Interaction Metrics:\")\n",
    "for key, value in results.items():\n",
    "    print(f\"{key}: {value}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Advanced Visualization: Interaction Metrics\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Information Tensor Heatmap\n",
    "plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)\n",
    "sns.heatmap(\n",
    "    results['InformationTensor'], \n",
    "    cmap='magma', \n",
    "    annot=True, \n",
    "    fmt='.4f', \n",
    "    cbar_kws={'label': 'Entropy-Encoded Coupling'}\n",
    ")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Information Tensor: Source Space vs Target Space\", fontsize=10)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Interaction Metrics Comparison\n",
    "plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)\n",
    "metrics = [\n",
    "    results['InteractionAction'], \n",
    "    results['EntropyLeak'], \n",
    "    abs(results['DirectionalCoherence'])\n",
    "]\n",
    "plt.bar(\n",
    "    ['Interaction Action', 'Entropy Leak', 'Coherence Magnitude'], \n",
    "    metrics\n",
    ")\n",
    "plt.title(\"CASP Interaction Metrics\", fontsize=10)\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Normalized Magnitude\")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🔍 Advanced CASP Evaluation Framework\n",
    "\n",
    "### Key Performance Metrics\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Interaction Action**: \n",
    "   - Quantifies cross-absolute engagement efficiency\n",
    "   - Lower values indicate more constrained interactions\n",
    "\n",
    "2. **Entropy Leak**: \n",
    "   - Ensures strict compliance with entropic compatibility\n",
    "   - Measures deviation from ideal informational symmetry\n",
    "\n",
    "3. **Directional Coherence**: \n",
    "   - Captures alignment of projected informational structures\n",
    "   - Indicates potential for meaningful cross-absolute interactions\n",
    "\n",
    "### Theoretical Significance\n",
    "These constraints constitute the **necessary and sufficient conditions** for ontologically valid absolute interactions.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Transition to Force Emergence\n",
    "If CASP is satisfied, the interaction is promotable to a force emergence tensor in subsequent computational stages.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Recommended Next Notebook:** `10_experimental_predictions.ipynb`"
   ]
  }
 ],
